y]]: at the end of Reasner Road, past Heath Road<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/RoseCity-MI.htm |title=Magnetic Hill \u2013 Rose City, Michigan |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Farmington Hills, Michigan|Farmington Hills]]: in Oakwood Cemetery, if you enter by the west gate and stop by a knotted tree, then put your car in neutral, it will appear to roll back uphill.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Michigan Graveyard Where your Car Rolls Back Uphill |url=http://99wfmk.com/oakwood-cemetery-farmington/ |website=99.1 WFMK |date=2019-07-02 |accessdate=2019-11-15}}</ref>\n\n===Minnesota===\n* 330th St and 660th Ave., [[Watkins, Minnesota|Watkins]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hauntedplaces.org/item/660th-ave-gravity-hill/|title=660th Ave \u2013 Gravity Hill|website=Haunted Places}}</ref> (Forest City Township)\n\n===Mississippi===\n*[[Burnsville, Mississippi|Burnsville]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onlyinyourstate.com/mississippi/gravity-hill-ms/|title=This Strange Phenomenon In Mississippi Is Too Weird For Words|website=OnlyInYourState}}</ref>\n\n===Missouri===\n*[[Freeman, Missouri|Freeman]]: southwest of town near the [[Kansas]] state line at the intersection of [[Missouri Route D]] (Route&nbsp;D) and East 299th Street. Just outside [[Louisburg, Kansas]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ghosttraveller.com/missouri.htm |title=Missouri |publisher=Ghosttraveller |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Montana===\n*[[Columbia Falls, Montana|Columbia Falls]]: The Montana Vortex<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.montanavortex.com/ |title=The Montana Vortex and House of Mystery |publisher=montanavortex.com |date= |accessdate=2015-03-25}}</ref>\n\n===New Jersey===\n*[[Franklin Lakes, New Jersey|Franklin Lakes]]: Ewing Avenue exit off [[New Jersey Route 208|Route&nbsp;208]] South<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==874 |title=Franklin Lakes, New Jersey 