]]: [[Laurel Caverns]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==3303 |title=Hopwood, Pennsylvania - Laurel Caverns - Cave Mini Golf |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===South Dakota===\n*[[Rapid City, South Dakota|Rapid City]]: Cosmos Mystery Area, {{convert|16|mi|km}} south of Rapid City on [[U.S. Route 16 in South Dakota|US&nbsp;16]], {{convert|6|mi|km}} from [[Mount Rushmore]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cosmosmysteryarea.com/ |title=Cosmos Mystery Area Home |publisher=Cosmosmysteryarea.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Texas===\n*[[El Paso, Texas|El Paso]]: Thunderbird Drive facing south<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==1298 |title=San Antonio, Texas \u2013 Ghostly Gravity Hill |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[San Antonio]]: Just east of the [[San Antonio Missions National Historical Park]] at the railway crossing at Villamain Road and Shane Road<ref>[http://www.snopes.com/horrors/ghosts/handprint.asp Helping Hands], [[Snopes.com]] (retrieved 21 August 2010)</ref>\n\n===Utah===\n*[[Salt Lake City]]: A few blocks northeast of the [[Utah State Capitol|Capitol]] building in Salt Lake City. A small road (Bonneville Boulevard) loops around a park called [[Memory Grove (Salt Lake City)|Memory Grove]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==1833 |title=Salt Lake City, Utah \u2013 Gravity Hill |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Virginia===\n*[[Danville, Virginia|Danville]]: Berry Hill Road ([[U.S. Route 311 in Virginia|US&nbsp;311]]/[[Virginia State Route 863 (Pittsylvania County, Virginia)|SR&nbsp;863]]) and Oak Hill Road ([[Virginia State Route 862|SR&nbsp;862]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlyinyourstate.com/virginia/strange-phenomenon-va/ |title=This Strange Phenomenon I