el |publisher=The Wide Awake Cafe |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005003540/http://www.thewideawakecafe.com/?cat=51 |archive-date=2011-10-05 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><!--BETTER REFERENCE NEEDED-->\n*[[Helena, Arkansas|Helena]]: Sulphur Springs Road<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/Helena-AR.htm |title=Gravity Hill \u2013 Helena, Arkansas |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===California===\n*[[Altadena, California|Altadena]], 1054 E. Loma Alta Dr.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hauntedlosangeles.blogspot.com/2013/03/los-angeles-gravity-hill.html|title=Haunted Los Angeles: Los Angeles Gravity Hill- Altadena, CA|last=Manofmystery24|date=8 March 2013|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Rohnert Park]] (in [[Sonoma County, California|Sonoma County]]): From [[U.S. Route 101 in California|U.S. Route&nbsp;101]] (US&nbsp;101) freeway, take Rohnert Park Expressway east to Petaluma Hill Road, Petaluma Hill Road south to Roberts Road, Roberts Road east to Lichau Road. At an iron gate with the words \"Gracias San Antonio\" is the start of the gravity hill section (on the western slope of [[Sonoma Mountain]] near the [[Fairfield Osborn Preserve]]).<ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/RohnertPark-CA.htm |title=Gravity Hill \u2013 Rohnert Park, Sonoma County, California |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date=2003-04-10 |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Santa Cruz, California|Santa Cruz]]: 465 Mystery Spot Road off Branciforte Drive near [[California State Route 17|State Route&nbsp;17]] (SR&nbsp;17) within the [[redwood]] forest. A tourist attraction called \"[[Mystery Spot]]\" is operated at the site.<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1111/1467-9280.00196 |author1=Shimamura, A.P.  |author2=Prinzmetal, W.  |lastauthoramp=yes|title=The Mystery Spot Illusion and its Relation to Other Visual Illusions |journal=Psychological Science |volume=10 |pages=501\u2013507 |year=1999 |issue=6 | url = http://socrates.berkeley.edu/~shimlab/1999_Shim-Prinz_MystSpot.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mysteryspot.com/|title=The Mystery Spot Official Website|website=The Mystery Spot Official Website}}</ref>\n*[[Whittier, California|Whittier]]: Site at cemetery in Whittier, on Workman Mill Road, near [[Rio Hondo College]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paranormal.about.com/library/blstory_december02_08.htm |title=Paranormal Story Archive - December 2002 - Page 8 - Cemetery Gravity Hill |publisher=Paranormal.about.com |date=2010-06-17 |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Florida===\n[[File:Spookhill.jpg|thumb|[[Spook Hill]], [[Lake Wales, Florida]]]]\n\n*[[Lake Wales, Florida|Lake Wales]]: [[Spook Hill]], [[U.S. Route 27 in Florida|US&nbsp;27]] between [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]] and [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/LakeWales-FL.htm |title=Spook Hill \u2013 Lake Wales, Florida |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Georgia===\n*[[Cumming, Georgia|Cumming]]: Booger Hill a.k.a. Booger Mountain<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==1796 |title=Cumming, Georgia \u2013 Booger Hill |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Fort Gaines, Georgia|Fort Gaines]]: Spook Hill, north of town<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tip/327 |title=Ft. Gaines, GA \u2013 Gravity Hill |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date=2007-12-18 |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Indiana===\n* [[Mooresville, Indiana|Mooresville]]: Gravity Hill<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tip/3299 |title=Mooresville, Indiana \u2013 Gravity Hill |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2013-07-11}}</ref>\n\n===Kentucky===\n*[[Covington, Kentucky|Covington]]: in [[Devou Park]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WM6TPG_Gravity_Hill_at_Devou_Park_Covington_KY |title=Gravity Hill at Devou Park - Covington, KY - Vortexes, Mystery Spots, and Gravity Hills on |publisher=Waymarking.com |date=2009-07-19 |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Princeton, Kentucky|Princeton]]: about {{convert|1|mi|km}} west of Princeton off [[U.S. Route 62 in Kentucky|US&nbsp;62]] lies a gravity hill on [[Kentucky Route 2618]] (KY&nbsp;2618). Vehicles stop in the tunnel that the [[Western Kentucky Parkway]] bridge creates and the vehicle will roll all the way to the end of the road at the stop sign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/Princeton-KY.htm |title=Gravity Hill \u2013 Princeton, Kentucky |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date=1941-02-15 |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Massachusetts===\n*[[Greenfield, Massachusetts|Greenfield]]: Shelburne Road facing east towards Greenfield immediately after the [[Massachusetts Route 2]] (Route&nbsp;2) overpass<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==6523 |title=Greenfield, Massachusetts \u2013 Gravity Hill |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Michigan===\n*[[Blaine Township, Michigan|Blaine Township]] (near [[Arcadia Township, Manistee County, Michigan|Arcadia]]): Putney Road south of its intersection with Joyfield Road.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/Arcadia-MI.htm |title=Gravity Hill \u2013 Arcadia, Michigan |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date=1994-11-27 |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref> Cars appear to roll toward the church at the intersection. <ref>{{cite web |last1=King |first1=Dominique |title=The mystery of Benzie County's Putney Road |url=https://www.midwestguest.com/2010/10/the-mystery-of-benzie-countys-putney-road.html |website=Midwest Guide |accessdate=28 September 2019}}</ref> Local legend claims the church is pulling sinners towards its doors for redemption.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gravity Hills in Michigan |url=http://michigansotherside.com/gravity-hills-in-michigan/ |website=Michigan's Otherside |accessdate=1 October 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Rose City, Michigan|Rose City]]: at the end of Reasner Road, past Heath Road<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/RoseCity-MI.htm |title=Magnetic Hill \u2013 Rose City, Michigan |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Farmington Hills, Michigan|Farmington Hills]]: in Oakwood Cemetery, if you enter by the west gate and stop by a knotted tree, then put your car in neutral, it will appear to roll back uphill.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Michigan Graveyard Where your Car Rolls Back Uphill |url=http://99wfmk.com/oakwood-cemetery-farmington/ |website=99.1 WFMK |date=2019-07-02 |accessdate=2019-11-15}}</ref>\n\n===Minnesota===\n* 330th St and 660th Ave., [[Watkins, Minnesota|Watkins]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hauntedplaces.org/item/660th-ave-gravity-hill/|title=660th Ave \u2013 Gravity Hill|website=Haunted Places}}</ref> (Forest City Township)\n\n===Mississippi===\n*[[Burnsville, Mississippi|Burnsville]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onlyinyourstate.com/mississippi/gravity-hill-ms/|title=This Strange Phenomenon In Mississippi Is Too Weird For Words|website=OnlyInYourState}}</ref>\n\n===Missouri===\n*[[Freeman, Missouri|Freeman]]: southwest of town near the [[Kansas]] state line at the intersection of [[Missouri Route D]] (Route&nbsp;D) and East 299th Street. Just outside [[Louisburg, Kansas]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ghosttraveller.com/missouri.htm |title=Missouri |publisher=Ghosttraveller |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Montana===\n*[[Columbia Falls, Montana|Columbia Falls]]: The Montana Vortex<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.montanavortex.com/ |title=The Montana Vortex and House of Mystery |publisher=montanavortex.com |date= |accessdate=2015-03-25}}</ref>\n\n===New Jersey===\n*[[Franklin Lakes, New Jersey|Franklin Lakes]]: Ewing Avenue exit off [[New Jersey Route 208|Route&nbsp;208]] South<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/tips/getAttraction.php?tip_AttractionNo==874 |title=Franklin Lakes, New Jersey \u2013 Gravity-Defying Exit Ramp |publisher=Roadsideamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Jackson Township, New Jersey|Jackson]]: New Prospect Road<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jacksonnjonline.com/2011/09/27/uncovering-gravity-hill-in-jackson-township-nj/27726/|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130126162032/http://www.jacksonnjonline.com/2011/09/27/uncovering-gravity-hill-in-jackson-township-nj/27726/|url-status=dead|title=Uncovering Gravity Hill in Jackson Township, NJ - Jackson Township NJ\u2026|date=26 January 2013|archivedate=26 January 2013|website=archive.is}}</ref>\n\n===North Carolina===\n*[[Boone, North Carolina|Boone]]: Mystery Hill<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mysteryhill-nc.com |title=Mystery Hill |publisher=Mysteryhill-nc.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Richfield, North Carolina|Richfield]]: Gravity Hill on Richfield Rd.  Local legends suggest paranormal causes for phenomenon.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlyinyourstate.com/north-carolina/gravity-hill-nc/ |title=This Strange Phenomenon In A North Carolina Town Is Too Weird For Words |publisher=OnlyInYourState.com  |accessdate=2016-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.catawbapioneer.com/paranormal-profile-gravity-hill/ |title=Paranormal Profile: Gravity Hill |publisher=Pioneer: The Student Newspaper of Catawba College |accessdate=2016-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wral.com/lifestyles/travel/video/14764668/ |title=Gravity Hill defies physics |publisher=WRAL |accessdate=2016-01-27}}</ref>\n*[[Scotland County, North Carolina|Scotland County]]: Gravity Hill<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laurinburgexchange.com/top-stories/7594/area-ghost-stories-plentiful|title=Area ghost stories plentiful|last=Exchange|first=Laurinburg|date=2016-10-31|website=Laurinburg Exchange|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-06}}</ref>\n\n===Ohio===\n*[[Kirtland Hills, Ohio|Kirtland Hills]]: King Memorial Road<ref>[http://members.tripod.com/snap7901/id37.htm Gravity Hill]{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n===Oklahoma===\n*[[Bartlesville, Oklahoma|Bartlesville]]: Gap Road<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.strangeusa.com/Viewlocation.aspx?id=7827 |title=Haunt in Haunted Hill Bartlesville, Ok 74006 Bartlesville, OKLAHOMA Washington Haunt |publisher=Strangeusa.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228033347/http://www.strangeusa.com/Viewlocation.aspx?id=7827 |archive-date=2013-12-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Springer, Oklahoma|Springer]]: Near [[Ardmore, Oklahoma|Ardmore]], on Pitt Road.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlyinyourstate.com/oklahoma/gravity-hill-ok |title=This Strange Phenomena in Oklahoma is Too Weird for Words |publisher=OnlyInYourState.com| date=|accessdate=2016-01-27}}</ref>\n\n===Oregon===\n*[[Gold Hill, Oregon|Gold Hill]]: the [[Oregon Vortex]]<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.oregonvortex.com/ |title=The Oregon Vortex and location of the House of Mystery |publisher=Oregonvortex.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n\n===Pennsylvania===\n*Near [[Lewisberry, Pennsylvania|Lewisberry]], [[York County, Pennsylvania|York County]], on Pleasantview Road (also rendered Pleasant View Road) at [[Pennsylvania Route 177]] (PA&nbsp;177)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/Harrisburg-PA.htm |title=Gravity Hill - Harrisburg - Pennsylvania |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[New Paris, Pennsylvania|New Paris]]: Gravity Hill Road (two gravity hills in this area)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/NewParis-PA.htm |title=Gravity Hill - New Paris -Pennsylvania |publisher=Eureka4you.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bedfordcounty.net/gravityhill/index.htm |title=GRAVITY HILL, Pennsylvan